1426":"1343–1426","1355–Female":"1355–Overleden","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1384–Female":"1384–Overleden","1280–Male":"1280–Overleden","1310–Female":"1310–Overleden","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1280":"1280","1426":"1426","1348":"1348","1379":"1379","Abt 1392":"circa 1392","Abt 1322":"circa 1322","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1343":"1343","about 1334":"circa 1334","about 1384":"circa 1384","Easby, Yorkshire, England":"Easby, Yorkshire, England","Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Easby, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Widdington Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Aske, Yorkshire, England":"Aske, Easby, Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1322–Abt 1392":"about 1322–about 1392","1322–1392":"1322–1392","1348–Male":"1348–Deceased","1343–1426":"1343–1426","1355–Female":"1355–Deceased","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1384–Female":"1384–Deceased","1280–Male":"1280–Deceased","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1280":"1280","1426":"1426","1348":"1348","1379":"1379","Abt 1392":"about 1392","Abt 1322":"about 1322","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1343":"1343","about 1334":"about 1334","about 1384":"about 1384","Easby, Yorkshire, England":"Easby, Yorkshire, England","Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Widdington Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Aske, Yorkshire, England":"Aske, Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Aske","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Staffordshire): topographic name from northern Middle English <i>ask</i> ‘ash tree’ (Old Norse <i>askr</i>), or a habitational name from Aske (North Yorkshire). Compare   Ash  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ash","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>asche</i> ‘ash tree’ (Old English <i>æsc</i>), hence a topographic name for someone living by an ash tree or a habitational name from any of the many places in southern and central England named with this word (Derbyshire, Dorset, Hampshire, Herefordshire, Kent, Surrey, Shropshire, Somerset, and elsewhere).","Americanized form of German   Asch   and   Esch  , the latter ultimately also of Swiss German origin (see   Oesch  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of French   Dufresne  , with the same meaning as 1 above."]},{"name":"Axe","meanings":["English (West Yorkshire, Lincolnshire): variant of   Aske   with metathesis of /sk/ to /ks/, spelled with an <i>x</i>.","English (Dorset, Somerset): habitational name from Axe Farm in Chardstock (Devon, formerly in Dorset), itself named for the river Axe, which forms part of the south-eastern boundary of Chardstock parish.","Americanized form of German   Axt   or perhaps of some other similar (like-sounding) surname."]}]},{"name":"Conan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Conán . In historical times, the name was borne by a 7th-century saint, bishop of the Isle of Man.  Sir Arthur Conan Doyle  (  1859–1930 ), creator of  Sherlock Holmes , was born in Edinburgh, of Irish stock. The science-fiction creation Conan the Destroyer owes more to the villain of legend than to the bishop or the writer. For the most part this name is of Irish origin; however, it was in use in Yorkshire, especially among the Askes and the Bartons, from the 12th to the 16th centuries. In this case, the name was derived from Conan, Earl of Richmond, and is of Breton origin."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conan de Aske was born about 1322, in Aske, Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Roger de Aske, was 44 and his mother, Christina, was 14. He married Alianore Widdrington in 1379, in Northumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died about 1392, in his hometown, at the age of 72."},"et":{"Abt 1322–Abt 1392":"umbes 1322–umbes 1392","1322–1392":"1322–1392","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1343–1426":"1343–1426","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1384–Female":"1384–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1310–Female":"1310–Surnud","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1280":"1280","1426":"1426","1348":"1348","1379":"1379","Abt 1392":"umbes 1392","Abt 1322":"umbes 1322","1355":"1355","1322":"1322","1310":"1310","1343":"1343","about 1334":"umbes 1334","about 1384":"umbes 1384","Easby, Yorkshire, England":"Easby, Yorkshire, England","Easby, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Easby, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Widdington Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, England","Aske, Yorkshire, England":"Aske, Easby, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1322–Abt 1392":"noin 1322–noin 1392","1322–1392":"1322–1392","1348–Male":"1348–Kuollut","1343–1426":"1343–1426","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1380–1440":"1380–1440","1384–Female":"1384–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1310–Female":"1310–Kuollut","1440":"1440","1384":"1384","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1280":"1280","1426":"1426","1348":"1348","1379":"1379","Abt 1392":"noin 1392","Abt 1322":"noin 1322","